@page "/about"

<h1>About</h1>


<div class="form-group">

    <p>
        Features:
        <ul>
            <li>Track bad days</li>
            <li>Add journal entries for each day</li>
            <li>Add expenses for the day</li>
            <li>Display total spent by month</li>
            <li>Add events for a day</li>
            <li>Track frequency of events</li>
        </ul>

    </p>

    <div class="card card-body">
        <strong>Instructions:</strong>
        <p>
            Click a day on the calendar to mark a bad day (red). Un-clicked days are marked as green automatically which means a good day.
        </p>

        <p>You can add a journal entry on any day to record any activities or thoughts.</p>

        <p>
            You can also add color coded events to a day to keep track of independently in the Statistics section.
            <br />
            Note: You must add the Event first from the Events section in order to add it to a day.
            <br /> <br />
            <i>All data is locally stored in your browser. Not saved anywhere else.</i>
        </p>
    </div>

</div>

